claim.claim-text:
10. An optical coupler, comprising:
an alignment sleeve configured to receive an optical package;
a housing;
a first lens at least partially disposed within the housing;
a second lens positioned proximate the first lens and at least partially disposed within the housing, wherein one of the first and second lenses is a half-ball lens; and
a barrel within which the housing is disposed, the barrel comprising:
a first receptacle proximate to the first lens and configured to receive an optical fiber; and
a second receptacle proximate to the second lens configured to receive the alignment sleeve.

23. An optical coupler, comprising:
a barrel;
a housing at least partially situated within the barrel;
a first lens at least partially situated within the housing;
a second lens at least partially situated within the housing;
a first receptacle defined in the barrel and configured to receive a ferrule having an optical fiber such that an end face of the optical fiber makes physical contact with a surface of the first lens when the ferrule is fully received within the first receptacle;
a second receptacle defined in the barrel; and
an optical package at least partially situated within the second receptacle.
